Reasoning: 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of encoding and transmission schemes for 360VR content, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper proposes a methodology for analyzing the geometric relations involved in assessing the quality of the viewport in 360VR content, which is related to graphics. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper's methodology involves analyzing the quality of the portion of the scene seen by users, which can be related to computer vision techniques. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the transmission of 360VR content, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper evaluates the performance of encoding and transmission schemes for 360VR content, which can be related to information theory.
